N2  - The article examines the influence of political activity during executive succession on post-succession outcomes. A discussion is presented about the influence of an organization's resource environment on a successor's political activity and the challenges faced by the successor in regard to resource acquisition and allocation activities. Details related to the involvement of a successor in general administrative activities are presented. The effects of political activity on organizational effectiveness is mentioned.
